6.  Statistical  research  methodologies  specialist  (national,  6  person-months).  The 
specialist should have an advanced university degree in statistical research with at least 8 years 
of experience in statistical research approaches and data analysis in the PRC. The specialist 
will have the following responsibilities: 
(i)  work together with the team leader, and refine the overall study framework and 
approach; 
(ii)  provide input to the design and implementation of pilot projects;   
(iii)  prepare related chapters or sections of TA documents and reports; 
(iv)  provide input to the inception, interim, and final TA reports; 
(v)  participate in TA workshops (inception, interim, and final); and  
(vi)  conduct other related work assigned by the team leader. 

7.  Environmental institutional and policy specialist (national, 7 person-months). The 
specialist should have an advanced university degree in environmental policy or a related field, 
with at least 8 years of experience in environmental institutional, policy, and legislation-related 
issues in the PRC. The specialist will have the following responsibilities: 
(i)  work together with the team leader, and refine the overall study framework and 
approach; 
(ii)  take  the  lead  in  preparing  the  detailed  action  plan  for  reforming  the 
environmental statistics system, and clarify short-term objectives and long-term 
tasks—the overall objective of this framework will be to outline all the detailed 
procedures and steps for environmental statistics reform; 
(iii)  prepare related chapters or sections of TA documents and reports; 
(iv)  provide input to the inception, interim, and final TA reports; 
(v)  participate in TA workshops (inception, interim, and final); and 
(vi)  conduct other related work assigned by the team leader. 

8.  The consultants will submit the following reports: (i) an inception report within a month 
after mobilization, (ii) an interim report 7 months after the TA commencement, (iii) a draft final 
report 15 months after TA commencement, (iv) a final report at the conclusion of the TA, and 
(v) the final draft of the policy brief knowledge product by the conclusion of the TA. The final 
report will reflect comments made by ADB, the government agencies, and other relevant parties. 
The consultants will submit all reports in English and Chinese languages—six copies each of 
the English and Chinese versions to the government; and three copies of the English version to 
ADB, including an electronic copy on a CD-ROM disk. The reports will be published in Chinese 
and in English languages, and made available online.
